The paper discusses the implementation of a multi-algorithm library in the Spark framework for machine learning, specifically deep learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of distributive computational abilities, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of advanced machine learning architecture suggests that the paper could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of real-world datasets, which could fall under the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for image recognition, which could fall under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
